##<a id="0-7-88"></a> v0.7.88

**Release Date:** March 6, 2020

<p class="note breaking"><strong>Breaking Change:</strong> This release is incompatible with the v0.6
  beta release of KSM.
  Before you install KSM v0.7, you must uninstall
  KSM v0.6 from <%= vars.ops_manager_full %>. After you install KSM v0.7,
  you must re-add your service offerings.
  </p>

### Features

New features and changes in this release:

* Upgrades from Helm 2 to [Helm 3](https://helm.sh/docs/faq/#changes-since-helm-2).
This means that KSM no longer installs Tiller onto the Kubernetes cluster.
Charts offered in KSM must be compatible with Helm 3.

* Moved KSM specific customizations out of the Helm chart and into their own directory.
This includes the plans, bind template, and cluster configuration.
This means that users needing to customize their service offering no longer need to repackage the Helm chart.

### Known Issue

This release has the following issue:

+ If your chart uses custom resources, KSM might incorrectly report that a service instance
was created successfully before the custom resources are created.
This is because Kubernetes does not have a generic method to detect resource readiness.
Kubernetes primitives have known patterns for detecting readiness, but the author defines the custom
resource readiness. <br><br>
In the unlikely event that this happens, wait until the custom resources are created before binding
a service instances to an app.
This mitigates any issues with missing details in the bind response.

+ Decreased KSM stability around BOSH process monitoring and restarting.

