### Features

New features and changes in this release:

* Platform operators can offer services that have multiple Helm charts.
* The KSM CLI replaces the Bazaar CLI.
* Binding credentials are automatically stored in runtime CredHub.
This requires KSM to be installed on a <%= vars.pas_short %> deployment
with CredHub enabled. For instructions about enabling CredHub, see
[Securing Services Instance Credentials with Runtime CredHub](https://docs.pivotal.io/pivotalcf/2-10/opsguide/secure-si-creds.html).

### Known Issues

This release has the following issues:

+ Binding credentials for service instances brokered by KSM are not consistently unique.
If more than one app is bound to the same service instance,
all of the apps use the same credentials to connect to the service instance.
If your binding credentials are compromised, you must rotate the binding credential for all the apps
that use the credential.

+ Users cannot store binding credentials with CredHub if the
**Include OpsManager Root CA in Trusted Certs** checkbox is not selected in BOSH Director.

